    <string name="privacy_local_content">All screenshots are processed locally on your device. The app does not proactively upload screenshots, logs, or device data to a remote server.\n\nPermissions (overlay, notification, Shizuku) are only used for scroll capture and status visibility. You can revoke them in system settings at any time.\n\nIf you manually check for updates, the app requests release metadata only. Screenshot content is not included.</string>
    <string name="install_local_content">Install steps:\n1. Install and start Shizuku.\n2. Open ScrollSnap and finish onboarding permissions.\n3. Tap \"Open Floating Button\" and grant overlay permission.\n4. Open your target page and tap the floating ball to start capture.\n5. Optionally add ScrollSnap to Quick Settings for fast toggling.\n\nTroubleshooting:\n- Cannot start capture: check Shizuku is running and permission is still granted.\n- Floating ball missing: verify overlay permission is not revoked.\n- Capture interrupted: slow down scrolling or adjust advanced stitch parameters.</string>
